political change while lee is the territorys most vocal advocate 
of sweeping democratic reform threeyearold meeting points goals 
include a high degree of self administration for the territory after 
1997 a central social security fund and more education subsidies 
yeung said 
lee believes the major issue dividing the parties will be whether 
they speak primarily for beijing or hong kong interests 
one big question is whether the chinese communist party in hong 
kong which now works behind the scenes will go above ground to 
openly participate in elections 
that would frighten the industrialists away immediately 
said lee 
despite the growing activity of local political groups harris 
sees little hope for them to wield real power noting that 
authoritarian communist countries such as china do not accept 
challenges to their rule 
