an earthquake with a preliminary reading of 51 on 
the richter scale shook a small island south of tokyo today the 
central meteorological agency said there were no immediate reports 
of damage or injuries 
the tremor which occurred at 1215 pm 1015 pm est sunday 
was centered at about 12 miles under the seabed south of miyake 
island about 100 miles south of tokyo the agency said 
it said another undersea earthquake of lesser magnitude hit the 
same area 36 minutes earlier no magnitude was available for the 
first quake 
the island is home to 4300 people 
the richter scale measures the magnitude of a quake at its 
epicenter according to ground motion as recorded on seismographs 
an earthquake of 5 on the richter scale is considered very 
strong a reading of 6 means severe and capable of widespread 
damage near the epicenter 
