americans generally agree that homelessness is 
widespread and worsening and most are dissatisfied with the 
governments response and would be willing to pay more taxes to 
combat the problem a poll has found 
a plurality of the 1084 adults surveyed in the media 
generalassociated press poll primarily faulted society rather than 
the homeless for homelessness 
