consumer group said monday 
in an analysis of the growing longterm care problem facing the 
nation and the major proposals in congress to address it consumers 
union recommends creation of a universal insurance program funded 
with taxes and premiums 
consumers unions criticism of private longterm health care 
insurance is based on a survey last may by consumer reports the 
groups producttesting publication but the health insurance 
association of america said the policies that were rated by the 
publication were old and are not representative of those being 
offered today 
consumers union outlined proposals for a basic program at four 
federal spending levels ranging up to 50 billion far more than 
the state and federal governments now spend on longterm care and 
said that even the more expensive proposals dont have to worsen the 
federal deficit 
revenue options include increasing the social security payroll 
tax establishing a broadbased payroll tax for longterm care 
imposing an income tax surcharge increasing gift and estate taxes 
raising alcohol or gasoline excise taxes and requiring payment of 
premiums 
we should not let the budget deficit be used as an excuse for 
