100 billion the new reagan budget projects a deficit assuming 
adoption of all its elements of 928 billion for 1990 down from 
an estimated 1615 billion deficit in the current fiscal year 
during his campaign bush advocated what he called a flexible 
freeze on federal spending the concept calls for holding the 
increase in overall spending at the annual rate of inflation 
currently running at about 44 percent 
any proposed additional increases would have to be offset by 
corresponding decreases in other programs except that social 
security benefits would not be touched 
bush will have to find room in the reagan budget outline for the 
increases in spending needed for the kinder gentler nation 
programs he proposed in his campaign including expected increases 
for education child care expansion of the governments head start 
