the navy said monday it has selected the 
general dynamics corp as the lead contractor on its next class of 
nuclearpowered attack submarine the ssn21 seawolf 
general dynamics victory over archrival newport news 
shipbuilding and drydock co came despite the fact that newport news 
earlier had won the lead contract for designing the hull of the new 
sub 
general dynamics has been designing the nuclear propulsion system 
for the new boat 
the navy said monday it was awarding general dynamics electric 
boat division in groton conn a 726 million 
fixedpriceincentive contract for the lead seawolf sub 
work will be performed in groton conn 67 percent quonset 
point ri 23 percent and charleston sc 10 percent and is 
expected to be completed in may 1995 the service said 
the navy declined to say what type of bid newport news had 
submitted in its competition with general dynamics 
the two shipyards compete annually to build the navys current 
class of attack submarine the socalled 688 or los angeles 
class newport news was the lead contractor on that class 
the navy expects to award its last two contracts for 688 subs in 
fiscal 1990 and then shift production entirely to the seawolf in 
fiscal 1991 by awarding contracts for two subs 
now that general dynamics has won the contract to build the lead 
boat newport news will not be in a position to compete in the 
program until those fiscal 1991 contracts are awarded 
the navy expects the new seawolf to help rebuild the us edge in 
underwater warfare an advantage eroded over the past decade 
because of espionage scandals and soviet efforts to build quieter 
submarines of their own 
the ssn21 like the 688class sub will be designed primarily to 
hunt and kill soviet submarines it is supposed to feature greater 
speed better sensors and longerrange weapons than the 688 class 
the seawolf is going to represent a major advance in speed 
depth quieting weapons capability and supportability the navy 
said monday 
