an indian woman says she is going to make 
the long flight home to her native country despite a fear of flying 
brought on by the loss of five members of her husbands family on 
pan am flight 103 
prachi dixits husband sunil a graduate physics student at the 
university of notre dame lost an aunt and uncle and three cousins 
when the pan am flight en route from london to new york exploded 
dec 21 over lockerbie scotland 
mrs dixit still plans to travel next month with her 20monthold 
son to her home in agra the site of the taj mahal 
she admits she is concerned about her safety on the 
transatlantic trip but that concern is tempered by the prospect of 
a family reunion and by her religious faith she said monday 
im excited to see my family she said 
i believe in god and that whatever he does is his decision so 
im not really worried about getting there she said 
still the tragedy of flight 103 is with her she returned last 
week from fairborn ohio and services for the members of her 
husbands family 
the uncle om dikshit a professor at wright state university 
his wife shanti their daughter garima rattan and her children 
anmol and suruchi boarded flight 103 in frankfurt west germany 
after apparently missing an earlier flight said mrs dixit she 
spells her name differently from her uncles 
for 20 hours we were told by pan am that they were not on the 
flight she said 
