something new has been added to your federal 
tax package but you probably should not take it too seriously 
as part of a government effort to reduce paperwork the internal 
revenue service now is required to estimate how much time it will 
take to fill out your return so on page 3 of your instruction 
booklet you will find a table estimating the average time required 
for recordkeeping learning about tax law or the form preparing 
the form and for copying assembling and sending the form to the irs 
the filer of a long form 1040 could be a fourmember family 
struggling to stay above the poverty line with 25000 income and 
no itemized deductions or the filer could be a millionaire whose 
stock transactions require a 100page document just to list 
nevertheless the irs estimates average all the 1040 filers 
together and recordkeeping will require 3 hours and 7 minutes 
learning about the law or the form 2 hours and 28 minutes 
preparing the form another 3 hours and 7 minutes and the rest of 
the work 35 minutes 
throw in a schedule a for itemized deductions and the average 
1040 filer is looking at 13 hours and 51 minutes 
