payment on modernizing and cleaning up the nations atomic weapons 
complex a job expected to cost 81 billion over the next 20 years 
in his proposed fiscal 1990 budget for the energy department 
which makes the nuclear bombs and warheads for the pentagon reagan 
asked for 3014 billion for moderninizing environmental and safety 
programs at the weapons plants that is 478 million more than is 
being spent on them this year 
</TEXT>
