<TEXT>
gte corp announced monday a 
reorganization into six operating groups and the appointment of kent 
b foster as president of the largest group gte telephone 
operations 
gte chairman and chief executive officer james l johnson said 
the six operating groups will report to president and chief 
operating officer charles r lee 
johnson said the new corporate structure was a natural step in 
the evolution of a more streamlined and efficient gte and is 
reflective of of the constantly changing business environment 
foster 45 most recently served as group vice president of 
telephone operations he began his career with gte in 1970 
last march gte began restructuring its telephone operations its 
largest business telephone operations account for about 12 billion 
of the companys 154 billion in annual revenues 
tony hamilton a gte spokesman said monday that the previous 
restructuring divided operations into two categories with a layer of 
staff support extending over both 
whats happening now is some are being split out from under 
telephone operations and the layer of staff support has been 
eliminated allowing each of these groups to report directly to the 
president the purpose of that is to make the responsiveness of each 
of these groups a little better a little faster he said 
the six operating groups their headquarters sites and presidents 
are 
gte telephone operations group irving texas foster consists 
of the domestic telephone operating units the general office 
british columbia telephone quebec telephone the dominican republic 
telephone co and data services 
gte electrical products group danvers mass dean t langford 
includes us lighting lighting international lighting products 
and precision materials 
gte government systems group waltham mass francis a gicca 
consists of three operating units command control and 
communications c3 systems electronic defense systems and tactical 
systems 
gte information services group tampa fla william e starkey 
consists of directories telecom commercial services education 
services health services and interactive services 
gte mobile communications group houston texas terry s 
parker includes mobilnet cellular communications crop airfone 
and paging 
gte spacenet group mclean va cj waylan includes gtes 
satellite launching and operations businesses 
gte is a worldwide corporation whose three core businesses 
telecommunications lighting and precision materials employ about 
161000 people in 44 states and 38 other countries 
