<TEXT>
ford motor co on monday recalled about 
300 of its 1988 heavyduty trucks to install parts omitted during 
assembly 
the automaker also recalled about 25000 of its mercury sable 
cars to change light bulbs in the vehicles side marker lamps 
ford said in a news release that the trucks 1988 models of the 
f250 hd fourwheeldrive vehicles were assembled without fuel 
reservoir shields which are required by federal safety standards 
the shield protects the fuel tank in a 30mph frontend crash 
the company said it knew of no accidents fires or injuries because 
of the omission in the trucks which are more than 8500 pounds in 
gross weight 
meantime the company also recalled 25000 sables because a clear 
bulb instead of an amber one was installed in side marker lamps 
owners of the affected vehicles will be notified by mail and 
problems will be corrected free of charge the company said 
